(140, 1, '2014-01-29 07:01:53', '2014-01-29 07:01:53', '<h1><strong>Training Methodology</strong></h1>\r\nCandidates are selected based on the essential qualification and age. During the personal interview the candidates are evaluted and if found suitable only they will be advised tojoin the Course.\r\n\r\nSenior Managers who worked more than 20 years in the relevant respective industry will alone handle classes in different verticals.\r\n\r\nClass Room: Lectures are done in usual power point presentation. There will be a test everyday based on the inputs given on the previous day.\r\n\r\nGroup Discussion: In order to improve communication skills group discussion is done very frequently.\r\n\r\nCase Studies: Always, learning will be much better through Case Study method. KVM Academy always understands the value of case and it is practised in the classes every alternate days.\r\n\r\nMock Interview: Reharsal is always a better tool to perform-So, in order to make the trainees more effective and successful during the interview with companies which will be arranged by KVMA -the Academy conducts freqent mock interview for the trainees so that they will perform effectively and get them placed.in the very first interview itself.\r\n\r\n<strong>After completing the class room training the candidates will unergo one month on the job training also with the companies.</strong>', 'Our Process', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'our-process', '', '', '2014-02-13 07:43:03', '2014-02-13 07:43:03', '', 0, 'http://kvmacademy.com/?page_id=140', 0, 'page', '', 0);
