(247, 1, '2013-02-23 08:02:25', '2013-02-23 08:02:25', '<div class="kvm-article">\r\n<p class="byline"><a href="http://newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article1474950.ece" target="_blank">By <span class="authorName">Express News Service - CHENNAI</span></a></p>\r\n<p class="publishedDateline"><a href="http://newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article1474950.ece" target="_blank">23rd February 2013 08:03 AM</a></p>\r\nWith poor perceptions plaguing pharma sales representatives who also have to contend with poor pay packages, here’s a measure that could come as a shot in the arm for those intending to be one. The KVM Academy,in concert with Franklin Covey India and South Asia, launched a four-month training course in pharma sales under healthcare vertical. The course is expected to begin in March at the Madras School of Social Work campus, and in another city in the state. Addressing the media, Dr Ramki Murugan, director education of KVM Academy, said that the course will comprise three months training in basics and a one-month on-the-job training. He said: “Students will be trained on the various technical aspects such as pyshchiatry, with Frankline Covey training them on vital issues such as soft skills and inter-personal skills.” The course proposes to admit 60 students in one batch.\r\n\r\nSpeaking on the occasion, MD of KVM Academy, K V Madhavan, said that the rationale behind setting up the academy was industry reports that stated that a good percentage of graduates remain unemployed. He also added that the company also  intends to start a one-year diploma course in this regard.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'Training course in pharma sales launched', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'training-course-in-pharma-sales-launched', '', '\nhttp://newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article1474950.ece', '2014-02-12 10:23:50', '2014-02-12 10:23:50', '', 0, 'http://kvmacademy.com/?p=247', 0, 'post', '', 0),
