video player\\&quot; width=\\&quot;588\\&quot; height=\\&quot;340\\&quot; src=\\&quot;http://www.youtube.com/embed/HkZKkwHwQvE\\&quot; frameborder=\\&quot;0\\&quot; allowfullscreen=\\&quot;\\&quot;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;'',''hspace'':null,''vspace'':null,''align'':null,''bgcolor'':null}" alt="" /></object>\r\n<h6 class="lightbg" style="padding: 15px;"><a title="KVM Academy on Ottaranchetti" href="http://www.ottrancheithi.com/business/franklin-covey-and-kvm-academy-education-initiative-press-meet/" target="_blank">Ottaranchetti </a>  <a title="KVM Academy on Direct Chennai" href="http://www.directchennai.com/tamil/current-news/franklincovey-ties-up-with-kvm-group-1579.html" target="_blank">Direct Chennai</a>    <a title="KVM Academy on Suleka" href="http://education.sulekha.com/franklincovey-kvm-academy-forge-exclusive-partnership-for-national-education_596911_blog" target="_blank">Sulekha</a>    <a title="KVM Academy on Metro News" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HkZKkwHwQvE" target="_blank">Metro News</a>    <a title="KVM Academy on Chennai News" href="http://www.chennaivision.com/news/2012/17080.php" target="_blank">Chennai Vision</a></h6>\r\n<h3>FranklinCovey India &amp; SouthAsia and KVM Academy forge exclusive partnership for a national education initiative through an MoU</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>‘KVM Academy’ aims to increase employability of graduates across sectors</li>\r\n	<li>By launching a one-year PG Diploma program catering to specific verticals</li>\r\n	<li>Guided by an Advisory Board &amp; an Academic Council constituting India’s most respected names</li>\r\n	<li>Providing readily employable executives to the industry</li>\r\n	<li>JV to be formed between KVM Academy &amp; FranklinCovey India &amp; SouthAsia</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Chennai, 19th December 2012:</h4>\r\nFranklinCovey ( India &amp; SouthAsia operations ) a leading global training and consulting institute, today announced an exclusive partnership with KVM Group, a leading project advisory and service provider in IT, Architecture and Trading, for the launch of FranklinCovey Post Graduate (PG) Diploma in association with KVM Academy – a national education initiative to address the growing challenge of skill development and employability across sectors. KVM Academy will be operational from July 2013.\r\nKVM Academy is the first ever initiative of its kind in India. The One-year “FranklinCovey Post Graduate (PG) Diploma” programs will be conducted across leading colleges in the country. The programs will not just constitute theoretical learning but also provide extensive soft &amp; behavoural skills training, focusing on communication , team working , leadership ,effectiveness , business acumen skills and more to empower the students to excel in their respective domains. The course will impart comprehensive knowledge fully supported by skills &amp; tool sets so that the knowledge can be effectively used and implemented in real life and at work to achieve desired results . The academy will be guided by an Advisory Board &amp; Academic Council with luminaries including Padma Bhushan Mr. N. Vittal (former Chief Vigilance Commissioner, Govt. of India), Mr. Mohan Lall (former Commissioner of IT), Mr Ravindra Gupta (former Chairman, BIFR), Mr. Bijon Nag (Chairman, IFB Industries) ,Mr. Rajan Kaicker (Executive Chairman and MD, FranklinCovey India &amp; SouthAsia) &amp; Mr. Lavleen Raheja ( Chairman &amp; CEO, FranklinCovey India &amp; SouthAsia )\r\nRationale for setting up the KVM Academy is validated by several industry reports. A McKinsey report finds that only 25% of the engineers, 15% of finance graduates and less than 10% of other graduates are employable out of the graduates who pass out of the colleges. It has also been reported that only 3.5% of India’s population graduates. If 90% of the graduates are unemployable, it means that barely 0.5% of India’s population comprises employable graduates! The National Skill Development Corporation (NSDC) puts the need for skilled hands in India at 530 million. With globalisation being a reality and foreign investments in India on the rise, the gap between the academia and corporates is increasing steadily.\r\n\r\n<strong>Mr. K.V. Madhan, Managing Director, KVM Group of Companies</strong>, said, “<strong><em>KVM Academy is an endeavour to prepare graduates for a world of opportunities by imparting industry-specific knowledge and skills. Both the CII and the Boston Consulting Group estimate that inability of educational institutions in India to impart vocational training will lead to a ‘talent gap’ of more than 5 million by 2012. Addressing the two urgent needs of India Inc., this initiative with FranklinCovey will precisely address the employability gap and help craft a holistic learning program for students.</em></strong>”\r\n\r\n<strong>Mr. Lavleen Raheja, Chairman &amp; CEO, FranklinCovey India &amp; SouthAsia</strong> said, “<strong>This challenging program will help the industry as much as it helps the students. The corporates get readily employable graduates which saves them money and time. And the students get an opportunity to specialize and get employed in a vocation of their choice – a clear example of Dr. Stephen Covey’s 4th habit of thinking Win-Win.”</strong>\r\n\r\nIn the first year, the PG Diploma program will be rolled out in 4 cities across India. The course will focus on verticals such as Financial Services, Banking, Insurance, Retail, Realty, SME Manufacturing, Hospitality &amp; Tourism and Healthcare &amp; Wellness. The program is designed for graduates who wish to pursue a career in their chosen areas of interest. While embarking on a career path, there could often be some confusion on which path to take. To clear this, the admission process will include an aptitude test and an interview to help the students decide what is best for them. This focus on the choice of students and the strong panel of subject matter experts is what gives KVM Academy the edge over others.\r\n\r\nKVM Academy is in the process of forging tie-ups with corporates and financial institutions for their executive requirements. This domain specialisation will remove the need for training new entrants in an organisation saving money and valuable time.\r\n<h4>About Franklin Covey :</h4>\r\nFranklinCovey Co. (NYS: FC) is a global company specializing in performance improvement. They help organizations achieve results that require a change in human behaviour. Their expertise is in seven areas: leadership, execution, productivity, trust, sales performance, customer loyalty and education. Franklin Covey clients have included 90 percent of the Fortune 100, more than 75 percent of the Fortune 500, thousands of small- and mid-sized businesses, as well as numerous government entities and educational institutions. Franklin Covey has more than 40 direct and licensee offices providing professional services in over 140 countries. For more information, visit <a href="http://www.franklincoveysouthasia.com">www.franklincoveysouthasia.com</a>  &amp;  <a href="file:///C:\\Users\\sohini%20shreyas\\AppData\\Local\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Temporary%20Internet%20Files\\Content.IE5\\RTSJUFPN\\www.franklincovey.com">www.franklincovey.com</a>\r\n<h4>About KVM Group of Companies :</h4>\r\nKVM Group is a leading project advisory and service provider in IT, Architecture and Trading. The foundation for KVM Group was laid in June 2009, when KV Madhan Advisory Services was formed. The Group has rapidly built a significant competitive presence in the country and operates from offices in Chennai, Delhi, Mumbai, Hyderabad and Bangalore. With around 40 experienced professionals on board to offer clients full range of services across various sectors. For further information visit: <a href="http://www.kvmadvisory.com">www.kvmadvisory.com</a>', 'Press Conference - Dec-19-2012', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '238-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-02-12 10:08:00', '2014-02-12 10:08:00', '', 238